headline: Indian Census Head Urges Drive For Birth Control to Bar Famines; INDIA DRIVE URGED FOR BIRTH CONTROL
snippet: NEW DELHI, India, Nov. 11 -The Indian Government has been urged in an official report to undertake an intensive birth control campaign to avert national disaster implicit in the rapidly growing population.

headline: INDIA SPURS START OF BIRTH CONTROL; Nation, With Population Gain of 4,000,000 a Year, to Launch Plan Ahead of Schedule
snippet: NEW DELHI, India, April 19 -- With her teeming population increasing at the rate of 4,000,000 a year, India is rushing to embark on a $1,300,000 birth-control program ahead of schedule.

headline: Birth Control bill, Referendum on Issue Favored by Connecticut Legislative Group
snippet: HARTFORD, April 15 -- The Joint Public Health and Safety Committee of the Connecticut General Assembly voted 11 to 8 today to favor a bill authorizing physicians to prescribe contraceptives for married women where their health was involved.
